assert_subset_suggest <- function(x, choices) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    142x

                    136
                    142x

                    148
                    2x

                    4x
                    
                      
      paste(

                    4x
                    
                      
        paste0(

                    4x
                    
                      
          "\n",

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    4x

                    153
                    4x
                    
                      
          " is not a valid argument."

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    
                    
                      
        ),

                    2x

                    2x

# egt03_1 ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#' @describeIn egt03_1 Main TLG function

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' @param arm_var (`character`) the arm variables used for row split, typically `"ARMCD"`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param summaryvar (`list`) variables to be analyzed, typically `"BNRIND"`. Names are used as

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' subtitles. For values

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#'   where no name is provided, the label attribute of the corresponding column in `adeg` table of `adam_db` is used.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param splitvar (`list`) variables to be analyzed, typically `"BNRIND"`. Names are used as

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' subtitles. For values

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#'   where no name is provided, the label attribute of the corresponding column in `adeg` table of `adam_db` is used.

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' @details

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'  * ADEG data are subsetted to contain only "POST-BASELINE MINIMUM" visit

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'  * the number of patients by baseline assessment and minimum post-baseline assessment.

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Percentages are based on the total number of patients in a treatment group.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Split columns by Analysis Reference Range Indicator, typically `ANRIND`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Does not include a total column by default.

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Sorted  based on factor level.

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' @note

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'  * `adam_db` object must contain an `adeg` table with a `"ARMCD"` column as well as columns specified in

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'  `summaryvar` and `splitvar`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
egt03_1_main <- function(adam_db,

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
                         arm_var = "ARMCD",

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
                         summaryvar = list("Baseline Reference Range Indicator" = "BNRIND"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
                         splitvar = list("Analysis Reference Range Indicator" = "ANRIND"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
                         deco = std_deco("EGT03"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
                         ...) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    1x
                    
                      
  summaryvar <- unlist(summaryvar)

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    1x
                    
                      
  splitvar <- unlist(splitvar)

                    		
                  

                  

                    34

#' `EGT03` Table 1 (Default) Shift Table of ECG Interval Data - Baseline versus Minimum Post-Baseline

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    
                    
                      
#' The `EGT03` Table entries provide the number of patients by baseline assessment and minimum post-baseline

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    
                    
                      
#' assessment. Percentages are based on the total number of patients in a treatment group. Baseline is the

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    
                    
                      
#' patient's last observation prior to initiation of study drug.

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    175

                    176

                    179
                    
                    
                      
#' db <- syn_data

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    
                    
                      
#' run(egt03_1, db)

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    
                    
                      
egt03_1 <- chevron_t(

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    
                    
                      
  main = egt03_1_main,

                    		
                  

                  

                    183

                    184
                    
                    
                      
  postprocess = egt03_1_post,

#' @describeIn egt03_2 Main TLG function

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    
                    
                      
#' @inheritParams gen_args

                    		
                  

                  

                    193
                    
                    
                      
#' @param arm_var (`string`) the arm variables used for row split, typically `"ARMCD"`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    
                    
                      
#' @param summaryvar (`list`) variables to be analyzed, typically `"BNRIND"`. Names are used as

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    
                    
                      
#' subtitles. For values

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    
                    
                      
#'   where no name is provided, the label attribute of the corresponding column in `adeg` table of `adam_db` is used.

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    
                    
                      
#' @param splitvar (`list`) variables to be analyzed, typically `"BNRIND"`. Names are used as

                    		
                  

                  

                    198

                    199

                    201
                    
                    
                      
#' @details

                    		
                  

                  

                    202
                    
                    
                      
#'  * ADEG data are subsetted to contain only "POST-BASELINE MAXIMUM" visit

                    		
                  

                  

                    203

                    204

                    205

                    206

# aet01_aesi_1 ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @describeIn aet01_aesi_1 Main TLG function

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @inheritParams gen_args

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param aesi_vars (`list`) the AESI variables to be included in the summary. Defaults to `NA`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param grade_groups (`list`) the grade groups to be displayed.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @details

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Does not remove rows with zero counts by default.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @note

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'  * `adam_db` object must contain an `adae` table with columns `"AEOUT"`, `"AEACN"`, `"AECONTRT"`, `"AESER"`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'  `"AREL"`, and the column specified by `arm_var`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'  * `aesi_vars` may contain any/all of the following variables to display: `"ALLRESWD"`, `"ALLRESDSM"`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'  `"ALLRESCONTRT"`, `"NOTRESWD"`, `"NOTRESDSM"`, `"NOTRESCONTRT"`, `"SERWD"`, `"SERDSM"`, `"SERCONTRT"`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'  `"RELWD"`, `"RELDSM"`, `"RELCONTRT"`, `"RELSER"`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'  * `aesi_vars` variable prefixes are defined as follows:

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'    * `"ALLRES"` = "all non-fatal adverse events resolved"

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'    * `"NOTRES"` = "at least one unresolved or ongoing non-fatal adverse event"

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#'    * `"SER"` = "serious adverse event"

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'    * `"REL"` = "related adverse event"

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'  * `aesi_vars` variable suffixes are defined as follows:

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'    * `"WD"` = "patients with study drug withdrawn"

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#'    * `"DSM"` = "patients with dose modified/interrupted"

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#'    * `"CONTRT"` = "patients with treatment received"

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Several `aesi_vars` can be added to the table at once:

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#'    * `aesi_vars = "ALL"` will include all possible `aesi_vars`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#'    * Including `"ALL_XXX"` in `aesi_vars` where `XXX` is one of the prefixes listed above will include all

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#'    `aesi_vars` with that prefix.

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
aet01_aesi_1_main <- function(adam_db,

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
                              arm_var = "ACTARM",

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
                              aesi_vars = list(NA_character_),

                    		
                  

                  

                    36

                    1x

lbt07_1_pre <- function(adam_db, ...) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    1x

check_all_colnames <- function(df, x, null_ok = TRUE, qualifier = NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    118x
                    
                      
  checkmate::assert_data_frame(df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    118x

                    17
                    118x

                    118x

    invisible(NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    24

                    25
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
}

dst01_1_post <- function(tlg, prune_0 = TRUE, deco = std_deco("DST01"), ...) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    1x

                    1x

                    1x

                    1x

                    200

                    1x
                    
                      
  std_postprocess(tbl)

dst01_2_pre <- function(adam_db,

                    		
                  

                  

                    383
                    
                    
                      
                        status_var = "EOSSTT",

                    1x

                    1x

                    1x

                    1x

#' DST01 Table 2 (Supplementary) Patient Disposition Table 2.

  main = dst01_2_main,

# dst01_3 ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    460
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    461
                    
                    
                      
#' @describeIn dst01_3 Main TLG function

                    		
                  

                  

                    462
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    463
                    
                    
                      
#' @inheritParams gen_args

                    		
                  

                  

                    464
                    
                    
                      
#' @param status_var (`string`) variable used to define patient status. Default is `EOSSTT`, however can also be a

                    		
                  

                  

                    465
                    
                    
                      
#'   variable name with the pattern `EOPxxSTT` where `xx` must be substituted by 2 digits referring to the analysis

                    		
                  

                  

                    466
                    
                    
                      
#'   period.

                    		
                  

                  

                    467
                    
                    
                      
#' @param disc_reason_var (`string`) variable used to define reason for patient withdrawal. Default is `DCSREAS`,

                    		
                  

                  

                    468
                    
                    
                      
#'   however can also be a variable with the pattern `DCPxxRS` where `xx` must be substituted by 2 digits referring to

                    		
                  

                  

                    469
                    
                    
                      
#'   the analysis period.

                    		
                  

                  

                    470
                    
                    
                      
#' @param status_treatment_var (`string`) variable used to define the treatment status of the patients. Default is

                    		
                  

                  

                    471
                    
                    
                      
#'   `EOTSTT`, however can also be a variable with the pattern `EOTxxSTT` where `xx` must be substituted by 2 digits

                    		
                  

                  

                    472
                    
                    
                      
#'   referring to the analysis period.

                    		
                  

                  

                    473
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    474
                    
                    
                      
#' @details

                    		
                  

                  

                    475
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Non-standard disposition table summarizing the reasons for patient withdrawal and treatment status.

                    		
                  

                  

                    476
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Withdrawal reasons are grouped into Safety and Non-Safety issues.

                    		
                  

                  

                    477
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Safety issues include Death and Adverse Events.

                    		
                  

                  

                    478
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Numbers represent absolute numbers of patients and fraction of `N`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    479
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Remove zero-count rows.

                    		
                  

                  

                    480
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Split columns by arm.

                    		
                  

                  

                    481
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Include a total column by default.

                    		
                  

                  

                    482
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Sort withdrawal reasons by alphabetic order.

                    		
                  

                  

                    483
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    484
                    
                    
                      
#' @note

                    		
                  

                  

                    485
                    
                    
                      
#'  * `adam_db` object must contain an `adsl` table with the column specified in `status`, `status_treatment` and

                    		
                  

                  

                    486
                    
                    
                      
#'  `disc_reason_var`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    487
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    488
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    489
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    490
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    491
                    
                    
                      
#' library(magrittr)

                    		
                  

                  

                    492
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    493
                    
                    
                      
#' db <- syn_data %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    494

#' dst01_3_main(db, lbl_overall = NULL)

dst01_3_post <- function(tlg, prune_0 = TRUE, deco = std_deco("DST01"), ...) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    662
                    1x
                    
                      
  tbl <- tlg[[1]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    663
                    1x
                    
                      
  tbl_completed <- tlg[[2]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    664
                    1x
                    
                      
  tbl_other <- tlg[[3]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    665
                    1x
                    
                      
  if (prune_0) tbl_other <- tbl_other %>% trim_rows()

                    		
                  

                  

                    666
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    667
                    1x
                    
                      
  col_info(tbl_other) <- col_info(tbl_completed)

                    		
                  

                  

                    668
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    669
                    1x
                    
                      
  tbl2 <- rbind(tbl_completed, tbl_other)

                    		
                  

                  

                    670
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    671
                    1x
                    
                      
  col_info(tbl) <- col_info(tbl2)

                    		
                  

                  

                    672
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    673
                    1x
                    
                      
  if (prune_0) tbl <- trim_rows(tbl)

                    		
                  

                  

                    674
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    675
                    1x
                    
                      
  tbl <- rbind(tbl2, tbl)

                    		
                  

                  

                    676
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    677
                    1x
                    
                      
  tbl <- set_decoration(tbl, deco)

                    		
                  

                  

                    678

                    1x
                    
                      
  std_postprocess(tbl)

                    		
                  

                  

                    680
                    
                    
                      
}

                    1x

                    7

                    18

#' @describeIn ext01_2 Main TLG function

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    
                    
                      
#' @inheritParams gen_args

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
#' @param summaryvars (`list`) variables to be analyzed. Names are used as subtitles. For values

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    
                    
                      
#'   where no name is provided, the label attribute of the corresponding column in `adex` table of `adam_db` is used.

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    
                    
                      
#' @details

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Supplementary Exposure table with binning of desired analysis values.

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    
                    
                      
#'  * The `n` row provides the number of non-missing values. The percentages for categorical variables is based on `n`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    
                    
                      
#'  The percentages for `Total number of patients with at least one dose modification` are based on the number of

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    
                    
                      
#'  patients in the corresponding analysis population given by `N`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Split columns by arm, typically `ACTARM`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Does not include a total column by default.

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Sorted by alphabetic order of the `PARAM` value. Transform to factor and re-level for custom order.

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
#'  * `ANL01FL` is not relevant subset

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
#' @note

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      
#'   * `adam_db` object must contain an `adex` table with columns specified in `summaryvars`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    153

  assert_colnames(adam_db$adex, summaryvars)

                    1x
                    
                      
  summaryvars_lbls <- get_labels(adam_db$adex, summaryvars)

                    1x

# pdt02_1 ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    2

#' @describeIn pdt02_1 Main TLG function

                    		
                  

                  

                    4

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @inheritParams gen_args

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param dvreas_var (`string`) the variable defining the reason for deviation. By default `DVREAS`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param lbl_dvreas_var (`string`) label for the variable defining the reason for deviation.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param dvterm_var (`string`) the variable defining the protocol deviation term. By default `DVTERM`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9

                    10

                    11

                    12

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'  `(AEPRELFL == "Y" & DVCAT == "MAJOR")`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Numbers represent absolute numbers of subjects and fraction of `N`, or absolute numbers when specified.

                    		
                  

                  

                    15

                    16

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'  * Does not include a total column by default.

                    		
                  

                  

                    18

                    19

                    20

                    21

                    23

                    24

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#'

# Chevron_tlg ----

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' `chevron_tlg` class

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' The `chevron_tlg` class associates a `preprocess` function, a main `tlg` function and `AdAM` tables names and

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' optionally a `postprocess` function.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @slot main (`function`) returning a `tlg`. Typically one of the `*_main` function from `chevron`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @slot preprocess (`function`) returning a pre-processed `list` of `data.frames` amenable to `tlg` creation. Typically

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'   one of the `*_pre` function from `chevron`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @slot postprocess (`function`) returning a post-processed `tlg`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @slot adam_datasets (`character`) representing the name of the tables from an `AdAM` dataset required for `tlg`

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'   creation.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' @format NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' @note To ensure the correct execution of the workflow additional validation criteria are:

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' * the first argument of the `main` function must be `adam_db`, the input `list` of `data.frames` to pre-process. The

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#' `...` argument is mandatory.

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' * the first argument of the `preprocess` function must be `adam_db`, the input `list` of `data.frames` to create

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' `tlg` output. The `...` argument is mandatory.

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' * the first argument of the `postprocess` function must be `tlg`, the input `TableTree` object to post-process. The

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' `...` argument is mandatory.

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#' @name chevron_tlg-class

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#' @exportClass chevron_tlg

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
.chevron_tlg <- setClass(

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
  "chevron_tlg",

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
  contains = "VIRTUAL",

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
  slots = c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
    main = "function",

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
    preprocess = "function",

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
    postprocess = "function",

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
    adam_datasets = "character"

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
)

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
